Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join, gradual curve. Clay fine buff; some mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 40. Name Exakestos. Nikandros group.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1701)
